Package: open-e-joviandss-proxmox-plugin
Version: 0.10.11
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3-oslo.utils (>= 3.36), python3-yaml (>= 3.13), multipath-tools, sg3-utils, python3-retry, libstring-util-perl
Maintainer: andrei.perepiolkin@open-e.com
Homepage: https://github.com/open-e/JovianDSS-Proxmox
Description: Open-E JovianDSS storage plugin for Proxmox VE
 This package provides seamless integration between Proxmox VE and Open-E
 JovianDSS storage systems via iSCSI protocol. The plugin enables automatic
 volume provisioning, snapshot management, and high-availability features.
 .
 Key features:
  * Thin provisioning with on-demand volume allocation
  * Storage-level snapshots with instant rollback capability
  * Multipath support for high availability and load balancing
  * Automated iSCSI target and LUN management
  * Support for VM live migration between Proxmox nodes
  * Integration with Proxmox backup and restore workflows
 .
 The plugin consists of a Perl storage plugin that integrates with Proxmox VE's
 storage framework and a Python CLI tool (jdssc) that communicates with the
 JovianDSS REST API for storage operations.
